-- Saudi Arabia Approves $1.6 Billion for Water Projects
-- B y   D e e m a   A l m a s h a b i
-- 2013-05-21T15:19:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-21/saudi-arabia-approves-1-6-billion-for-water-projects.html
Saudi Arabia ’s Water and Electricity
Ministry approved more than 5.9 billion riyals ($1.6 billion) in
spending for water and sanitation projects in Jazan on the Red
Sea coast,  state-owned Saudi Press Agency  reported.  The ministry has 254 water projects pending across the
kingdom for 2013, according to SPA’s  official website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Deema Almashabi in Riyadh at 
